author: HelloFresh
---

Wash and dry produce. TIP: Thoroughly pat lettuce dry before assembling salad.

Pat @fully cooked chicken breasts{8.6%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Thinly slice
crosswise into strips and place in a large #microwave-safe bowl{}. Add a drizzle
of @cooking oil{1%tsp}, @fajita spice blend{1/2%tbsp}, @salt{}, and
@pepper{}; stir to combine.

Cover with #plastic wrap{}; microwave until chicken is warmed through,
~{90%seconds}.

Meanwhile, trim and discard root end from @baby lettuce{1}; roughly chop. Dice
@tomato{1} into ½-inch pieces.

Place lettuce, tomato, and chicken in a second large #bowl{}; crush
@blue corn tortilla chips{3/4%ounce} over top. Drizzle with as much
@honey dijon dressing{1.5%ounce} as you like; toss to combine.

Divide salad between shallow bowls and serve with remaining
@blue corn tortilla chips{3/4%ounce} on the side.